My Prompts
Prompt 1:
I’m creating a landing page for my graphic design business. Can you suggest 3 service packages with descriptions and pricing? Please make them sound professional and appealing to clients.

Prompt 2:
Write the HTML code for a 'Services' section of a landing page for a graphic designer. Include 3 service offerings with their names, descriptions, and prices. Style them as cards inside a section with an <h2> title.

Prompt 3:
Generate CSS styles for a services section on a portfolio landing page. Each service should be in a card with padding, rounded corners, hover animation, and use these brand colors: dark red (#E51010), lime green (#C3FF83), black, and white.

AI Responses
Got it 👍 Let’s build this **step by step** so you can do everything **directly on GitHub’s web platform** (without creating local files). I’ll show you exactly how to set up your repo, publish with GitHub Pages, and structure your landing page.

---

## 🔹 Step 1: Create Your Repository

1. Go to [GitHub](https://github.com) and log in.
2. Click the **+** icon (top right) → **New repository**.
3. Name it something like `social-media-landing-page`.
4. Set it to **Public** (GitHub Pages requires public repo unless you have Pro).
5. Click **Create repository**.

---

## 🔹 Step 2: Add Your Files (Directly in GitHub)

1. Inside your new repo, click **Add file → Create new file**.
2. Name it `index.html`.
3. Paste the following code into it (I’ll mark AI-assisted sections in comments as required by your assignment).

---

### 📄 `index.html`

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Ty Phillip | Graphic Designer</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Navigation -->
  <nav class="navbar">
    <h1 class="logo">Ty Phillip</h1>
    <ul class="nav-links">
      <li><a href="#services">Services</a></li>
      <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://instagram.com" target="_blank">Instagram</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://tiktok.com" target="_blank">TikTok</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://linkedin.com" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>

  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <header class="hero">
    <h2>You think it, I make it.</h2>
    <a href="#services" class="cta-btn">View Services</a>
  </header>

  <!-- Services Section -->
  <section id="services" class="services">
    <h2>Our Services</h2>
    <div class="service-card">
      <h3>Logo & Brand Identity Package</h3>
      <p>What’s included: Custom logo design, color palette, and typography guide to define your brand’s unique look.
💰 $500 – one-time</p>
    </div>
    <div class="service-card">
      <h3>Social Media Graphics Bundle</h3>
      <p>What’s included: 15 branded templates (for Instagram, TikTok, LinkedIn, or Facebook) optimized for engagement and consistency.
💰 $350 – per bundle</p>
    </div>
    <div class="service-card">
      <h3>Marketing Collateral Design</h3>
      <p>What’s included: Professionally designed flyers, brochures, or business cards tailored to your campaign or product launch.
💰 Starting at $250 per project</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact Section -->
  <section id="contact" class="contact">
    <h2>Let’s get in touch</h2>
    <p>Tell me a little bit about your project below, or email me directly at 
      <a href="mailto:tykmwphillip@gmail.com">tykmwphillip@gmail.com</a>.</p>
    
    <!-- AI-Assisted Code: Contact Form -->
    <!-- This form structure was generated with AI assistance -->
    <form class="contact-form" action="https://formspree.io/f/mrblwjnk" method="POST">
      <label for="name">Name</label>
      <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>

      <label for="email">Email</label>
      <input type="email" id="email" name="_replyto" required>

      <label for="service">Select Service</label>
      <select id="service" name="service">
        <option>Logo & Brand Identity Package</option>
        <option>Social Media Graphics Bundle</option>
        <option>Marketing Collateral Design</option>
      </select>

      <label for="message">Message</label>
      <textarea id="message" name="message" required></textarea>

      <button type="submit" class="submit-btn">Submit</button>
    </form>
    <p class="form-msg">Thank you for your interest! Please allow 1-3 business days for an answer.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="footer">
    <p>© 2025 Ty Phillip | All Rights Reserved</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

---

### 📄 `style.css`

Now create another file: **Add file → Create new file → `style.css`**.
Paste this code:

```css
/* Global Styles (AI-assisted styling for colors & layout) */
body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  margin: 0;
  background-color: #000;
  color: #fff;
}

a { color: #C3FF83; text-decoration: none; }

/* Navbar */
.navbar {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  background: #E51010;
  padding: 1rem 2rem;
}
.navbar .logo { color: #fff; }
.nav-links { list-style: none; display: flex; gap: 1rem; }

/* Hero Section */
.hero {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #E51010, #000);
}
.cta-btn {
  background: #C3FF83;
  color: #000;
  padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 5px;
  transition: transform 0.3s;
}
.cta-btn:hover { transform: scale(1.1); }

/* Services */
.services {
  padding: 3rem 2rem;
  text-align: center;
}
.service-card {
  background: #111;
  margin: 1rem auto;
  padding: 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 10px;
  max-width: 500px;
  border: 2px solid #E51010;
}

/* Contact */
.contact { padding: 3rem 2rem; text-align: center; }
.contact-form {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  max-width: 500px;
  margin: auto;
  gap: 1rem;
}
.contact-form input,
.contact-form select,
.contact-form textarea {
  padding: 0.7rem;
  border: 1px solid #C3FF83;
  border-radius: 5px;
}
.submit-btn {
  background: #E51010;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 0.8rem;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background 0.3s;
}
.submit-btn:hover { background: #C3FF83; color: #000; }

/* Footer */
.footer {
  background: #111;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 1rem;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
}
```

---

## 🔹 Step 3: Enable GitHub Pages

1. In your repo → click **Settings** → **Pages**.
2. Under “Branch,” select **main** and **/root**.
3. Save → GitHub will give you a **public URL** (your live site 🎉).

